Kraken is one of the most established cryptocurrency exchanges in the world, trusted by institutions and individual traders, and known for its deep liquidity and trading infrastructure.



For this hackathon, participants will work with two Kraken products:

• Kraken CLI is an AI-native command-line interface for programmatic trading. It's a zero-dependency binary with a built-in MCP server, handling all exchange complexity (authentication, rate limiting, order management) so you can focus entirely on building your agent's strategy logic.

• xStocks are 1:1 asset-backed tokenized U.S. equities and ETFs that can be traded 24/7 on-chain. Using the Kraken CLI as the execution layer, participants can design strategies that autonomously buy, sell, and manage positions without handling complex exchange integrations.



Challenge:

Build an autonomous AI agent that trades xStocks: tokenized U.S. stocks and ETFs, using the Kraken CLI as its execution layer.

 
Your agent should analyze market signals, form a strategy, and execute trades programmatically without manual intervention. Whether you build a momentum-based stock picker, a portfolio rebalancer, or an event-driven trading system. The goal is a working agent that makes real decisions and trades real positions. 


✅ How Agents Are Ranked:
Agents in the Kraken Challenge are evaluated across two independent categories.



1️⃣ Trading Performance (PnL)
Agents are ranked purely by net PnL (realized + unrealized) over the competition period



How it works:

• Submission: Each participant provides a read-only Kraken API key linked to their trading account. This allows lablab.ai and Kraken to view trade history, no execution or withdrawal access is granted

• Audit: Kraken performs a final audit on top agents before prizes are distributed.
• Ranking: Winners are determined solely by net PnL at the end of the competition window. 


Requirements:

• Agents must use Kraken CLI as the execution layer
• One submission per participant or team


2️⃣ Social Engagement
Build in public. Share your journey. Inspire the community.



Over a 30-day window, participants earn a Social Engagement Score based purely on quantitative metrics from public platforms: Twitter/X, YouTube, blogs, or other channels.



How Winners are Determined:
• lablab.ai tracks engagement metrics: impressions, likes, shares, and reach across linked social accounts
• Rankings are determined purely by quantitative data: no subjective judging
• Participants can monitor their position throughout the competition window


